deck: A private school for young students! The Ducard Academy is led by a mysterious figure and Professor Hugo Strange, and they support and promote bad behavior by all means. It is up to young Bruce, Clark, and Diana to investigate what's really going on, who's the principal, and what's the secret behind "Nanda Prabat?"
description:
Spoiler Alert!!!

Some of the names and their roles are not revealed until the end of the first book - DC Comics: Secret Hero Society #1 - Study Hall of Justice.

The Ducard Academy

This is a list of characters and their roles - from students to principal - in the Ducard Academy?

Students (good):

  • Bruce Wayne
  • Clark Kent
  • Diana Prince

Students (bad):

  • Lex Luthor - Best science student and class president.
  • Bane - Main bully.
  • Joe Kerr - Main prankster.
  • Circe
  • Pamela Isley (Poison Ivy)
  • Selina Kyle (Catwoman)
  • Talia Al Ghul
  • Victor Fries (Mr. Freeze)
  • Harley Quinn (not mentioned by name)
  • Random clowns harassing Bruce, mostly.

Students who are only seen in costume during a Halloween party:

  • Oswald Cobblepot (Penguin) (also mentioned by name)
  • The Riddler
  • Scarecrow

Students who are only mentioned on various Valentine's Day cards sent to Bruce:

  • Bekka
  • Dinah Lance (Black Canary)
  • Zatanna

School Newspaper Staff of the Ducard Daily:

  • Victor Fries - Meteorologist/Weather Forecast
  • Circe - Horoscope aka "Horror Scopes"
  • Pamela Isley - Staff Environmental Reporter
  • Clark Kent - Apprentice who's articles are mostly ignored or moved to the last page.

Teachers & Coaching Staff:

  • Coach "Kitty" Faulkner (Rampage) - Girls' PE
  • Coach Zod - Boys' PE
  • Ms. Siobhan McDougal (Silver Banshee) - Choir
  • Mr. Basil Karlo (Clayface) - Theater & Arts
  • Mr. Jervis Tetch (Mad Hatter) - Literature
  • Mr. Vandal Savage - History
  • Dr. Thaddeus B. Sivana - Science

Administration & Management:

  • Brainiac - The academy's A.I. of sorts.
  • Mr. Solomon Grundy - Homeroom
  • Professor Hugo Strange - School Administration / Guidance Counselor
  • Ra's Al Ghul - Principal

Others:

  • Alfred Pennyworth
  • Krypto*
  • Ninja Patrols (guarding the Ducard Acadamy)
  • Vic Sage/The Question - Private Investigator

*Krypto is only seen cuddled by Clark on a holiday postcard from Smallville.
name: Ducard Academy

description: Augusta is the principal city of the Richmond County Metropolitan Statistical Area, which as of 2012 had an estimated population of 580,270, making it the third-largest city and the second-largest metro area in Georgia after Atlanta. It is the 116th-largest city in the United States. Internationally, Augusta is best known for hosting The Masters golf tournament each spring. It is also associated along with the United States Army base Fort Gordon.
